---
---

<section class="py-24 md:py-36 bg-warm-cream">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">

    <div class="max-w-3xl">
      <p class="text-storehouse-600 font-semibold text-sm tracking-widest uppercase reveal">
        The conversation
      </p>
      <h2 class="mt-4 font-display text-3xl sm:text-4xl text-text-deep leading-[1.05] reveal reveal-delay-1">
        Bob did something nobody else was doing.
      </h2>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-12 grid lg:grid-cols-12 gap-12 lg:gap-16">

      <!-- Prose column -->
      <div class="lg:col-span-7 space-y-6 text-lg text-text-body leading-relaxed reveal reveal-delay-2">
        <p>
          Most agents ask what you're looking for in a house. Bob asked
          about my life. Before we looked at a single listing, he spent
          nearly an hour learning about me &mdash; my work, whether I
          enjoyed it, where my family lived, how often I visited, my
          hobbies. He even asked about my golden retriever.
        </p>
        <p>
          Then he sat me down in his office with a printing calculator
          &mdash; the kind with the paper tape. This was pre-Zillow.
          MLS listings were physically printed every week. There were
          no apps, no algorithms, no instant pre-approval letters.
        </p>
        <p>
          Bob didn't just run the mortgage numbers. He calculated what
          my actual life would cost at $250,000 versus $127,000. Taxes,
          insurance, utilities, groceries, gas for the five trips a
          year to see my parents in Charleston, maintenance for the
          Jeep, food and vet bills for Roxanne. Emergency savings.
          Everything.
        </p>
        <p>
          Then he laid both numbers side by side and let me see the
          difference for myself. No pressure. No judgment. He just
          showed me.
        </p>
        <p>
          It would take me more than twenty years to discover the one
          word that perfectly captured what Bob was teaching me that
          day. But I didn't need the word yet. I just knew he was right.
        </p>
        <p>
          I bought the modest starter home. And for the first time, I
          had room to breathe.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Quotes column -->
      <div class="lg:col-span-5 space-y-8">

        <!-- First Bob quote -->
        <div class="relative reveal reveal-delay-2">
          <div class="bg-warm-white rounded-2xl p-8 border-l-4 border-l-storehouse-500 border border-storehouse-100/40">
            <span class="block font-quote text-5xl text-storehouse-400/30 leading-none select-none -mb-2" aria-hidden="true">&ldquo;</span>
            <p class="font-quote text-lg sm:text-xl text-text-deep italic leading-snug">
              The bank only cares if you can make this month's payment. I
              care if you can make it for 360 months while still having a
              life worth living.
            </p>
            <div class="mt-4 flex items-center gap-3">
              <div class="w-8 h-px bg-storehouse-300"></div>
              <p class="text-sm text-text-muted font-medium">Bob</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Second Bob quote -->
        <div class="relative reveal reveal-delay-3">
          <div class="bg-warm-white rounded-2xl p-8 border-l-4 border-l-gold-500 border border-storehouse-100/40">
            <span class="block font-quote text-5xl text-gold-400/40 leading-none select-none -mb-2" aria-hidden="true">&ldquo;</span>
            <p class="font-quote text-xl sm:text-2xl text-text-deep italic leading-snug">
              The cost of wants can sometimes outpace the cost of needs.
            </p>
            <div class="mt-4 flex items-center gap-3">
              <div class="w-8 h-px bg-gold-400"></div>
              <p class="text-sm text-text-muted font-medium">Bob</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>

    </div>

  </div>
</section>
